ingredients.ingredient: 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, or as needed
16 (6 inch) corn tortillas, or more to taste
4 boneless skinless chicken thighs, cut into chunks
½ cup diced mild green chiles
1 (28 ounce) can green chile enchilada sauce
1 (8 ounce) package shredded Monterey Jack cheese
4 ounces shredded mozzarella cheese, or more to taste

cookingTips: Lightly fry tortillas in oil for 10-15 seconds per side to soften them without making them crispy
Build stacks by alternating sauce, tortilla, and filling for even distribution and cooking
enrichment.coachingPrompt: How does the stacked presentation of enchiladas differ from rolled versions in both assembly and cooking?
